My current workaround to make the image smaller, since I have multiple to show, is to place the images in a table.</p>

<h2 id="2023-06-13-mathjax-doesnt-work-correctly">2023-06-13: Mathjax doesnâ€™t work correctly</h2>

<p>In the above the \(\int_{-\infty}^\infty \mathrm e^{-x^2}\, \mathrm dx = \frac\pi2\) renders fine only locally. Hereâ€™s a test with the backslash:
\(\int<em>{-\infty}^\infty \mathrm e^{-x^2}\, \mathrm dx = \frac\pi2\)
which also works locally. Display math with <code class="highlighter-rouge">\[...\]</code> also seems to work locally. \[\int</em>{-\infty}^\infty \mathrm e^{-x^2}\, \mathrm dx = \frac\pi2\]. But only locally.</p>

<p>Need to figure out how to make it workâ€¦</p>

<h2 id="2023-06-26-mathjax-is-working-correctly">2023-06-26: Mathjax is working correctly</h2>

<p>I followed the <a href="https://docs.mathjax.org/en/latest/web/start.html">Mathjax 3 documentation</a> and it now works.
Iâ€™m using the configuration block from <a href="https://docs.mathjax.org/en/latest/options/input/tex.html?highlight=displaymath#the-configuration-block">this part</a> of the docs.
Specifically, in <code class="highlighter-rouge">_includes/header.html</code>, I have put</p>

<div class="language-javascript highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="c">&lt;!--</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="nx">mathjax</span> <span class="nx">support</span> <span class="o">--&gt;</span>

